==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Dammara
<hw>Dam"ma*ra</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
}</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jav. & Malay. <ets>damar</ets>.]</ety>
<def>An oleoresin used in making varnishes; dammar gum; dammara resin.
It is obtained from certain resin trees indigenous to the East Indies,
esp. <spn>Shorea robusta</spn> and the dammar pine.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Dammar pine</b></col>, <fld>(Bot.)</fld>, <cd>a tree of
the Moluccas (<spn>Agathis orientalis</spn> syn. <spn>Dammara
orientalis</spn>), yielding dammar.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dammara</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dammara
<hw>Dam"ma*ra</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A large tree of
the order <ord>Conifer⟦ae⟧</ord>, indigenous to the East Indies and
Australasia; -- called also <altname>Agathis</altname>. There are
several species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Damn</ent>⟦br⟧
